fter Closing.";i:49;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:50;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:51;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:52;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:53;s:62:"If anything enters the beam even briefly the door opens again.";i:54;s:22:"Check Everything Over.";i:55;s:66:"Firstly do a quick look over the door and the automatic mechanism.";i:56;s:144:"When a garage door opens on its own the issue might be a loose wire in the motor or the sensor may be stopping the door from closing completely.";i:57;s:19:"Garage Door Opener.";i:58;s:27:"Opens and closes by itself.";i:59;s:162:"When your garage door opens or closes when you havent triggered the remote one possible cause is that a neighbors remote was programmed at the same time as yours.";i:60;s:53:"Erase all codes in your remote and then reprogram it.";}}